      • timeSignature

        private int[] timeSignature
        timeSignature[0] is the counter, timeSignature[1] the denominator, i.e., for a waltz it's usually 3 and 4 respectively. Default is 4/4.

      • scheduleEvent

        public void scheduleEvent(int barNumber,
                          double denominatorOffset,
                          int channel,
                          int volume,
                          Note note)
        schedules a new midi event
        Parameters:
        barNumber - the bar number where the note shall be played starting with 1
        denominatorOffset - the multiples of the denominator in the bar, e.g., for a 4/4 beat, a value of 3 will schedule the note to be played on the "3"
        channel - midi channel to be used
        volume - volume of the tone
        note - the midi note which shall be played
